      "content": {
        "title": "Nucleotide Components and Linkage",
        "definition": "Monomeric units of nucleic acids consisting of a nitrogenous base, a pentose sugar, and one or more phosphate groups linked by 3′–5′ phosphodiester bonds in polynucleotide chains.",
        "summary": "Nucleotides are the building blocks of DNA and RNA. Phosphodiester linkages connect the 3′ carbon of one sugar to the 5′ carbon of the next, defining strand polarity."
      },
