      "content": {
        "title": "RNA Structure and Single-Stranded Conformation",
        "definition": "RNA as a typically single-stranded polynucleotide with a 2′ hydroxyl group on ribose, uracil replacing thymine, and intramolecular base pairing forming hairpins and other secondary structures.",
        "summary": "RNA's 2′-OH increases reactivity and enables diverse folding. Secondary structure through local base pairing is essential for tRNA, rRNA, and regulatory RNAs."
      },
