        "title": "Factors Affecting Hybridization Stringency",
        "definition": "Experimental variables including temperature, salt concentration, and denaturants that control the specificity of complementary nucleic acid strand reannealing during hybridization.",
        "summary": "Higher stringency favors perfect matches over partial complementarity. Stringency is tuned in PCR annealing steps, Southern/Northern blots, and microarray hybridizations."
